@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(CMP-VALIDATE-CLI, 0015)
' @id(CMP-VALIDATE-CLI)
' @desc(CMP-VALIDATE-CLI, "The `mdd validate` subcommand in crates/mdd-cli/src/main.rs: the Commands::Validate { json: bool } variant and its match arm. The arm discovers the Project, calls Project::validate() (the deterministic engine in mdd-core — not reimplemented), and renders the ValidationReport: --json prints a slim json!({ok, errors, warnings}) via serde_json (registry excluded), text mode prints lines + a PASSED/FAILED summary, and it exits non-zero on !ok. A thin presentation layer over mdd-core, mirroring Commands::Review / Commands::MapStatus / Commands::Context; serde_json is a new mdd-cli dependency. It does not call review.")
' Current ownership (cycle 0015). Verdict logic stays in mdd-core
' (Project::validate, tested); the CLI adds only an entry point and
' output formatting. No new engine, no review coupling.
title MDD validate CLI — ownership (current)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

component "mdd validate [--json]\n(CMP-VALIDATE-CLI)\nmdd-cli/src/main.rs" as Cli
component "Project::validate()\nstructural engine\n(mdd-core)" as Engine
component "ValidationReport\n{ok, errors, warnings}" as Report
component "slim JSON view\n(serde_json)" as Json

Dev --> Cli : mdd validate [--json]
Cli --> Engine : validate()
Engine --> Report : ok / errors / warnings
Cli --> Report : read for text output
Cli --> Json : --json -> {ok, errors, warnings}

note bottom of Cli
  Thin presentation layer, like Commands::Review and
  Commands::Context. Exit 1 on !report.ok; warnings
  printed but never block. Independent of `mdd review`.
end note
@enduml
